comment._content: DUPLEIX "The M. M. Company's steamer Dupleix was moved from moorings off Fitzroy Dock to the company's wharf, Circular Quay, yesterday." - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/13675653 So October / November 1887 for date (?)

comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: "Launched July 27, 1862 in La Ciotat. First in a series of three identical vessels with MEINAM and LA BOURDONNAIS . Starts on the Levant, until 1865, and then opens the Shanghai-Yokohama line in 1865. In 1870-1871, he stays on the line of the Levant, and then returns to Marseille to be transformed (lengthening the hull, lengthening Abant forecastle, poop and installation of a roof derrère the mainmast, processing machines) . From 1873 he was assigned as stationary on adjacent lines of Madagascar and the Indian Ocean. In 1886 it is stationary on the Noumea-Sydney line. Sold in Sydney in December 1888 in the Co. Hon. JC Ellis and renamed JUBILEE before being profoundly transformed to liaise with Tasmania. sold in 1889 to JP Franki. Demolished in August 1898 in Sydney." [GoogleTranslate] from - www.messageries-maritimes.org/dupleixI.htm (in French)
